SUMMARY:Trashion Barbies &amp; Bags at Sonoma Community Center
DESCRIPTION:Trashion Fashion Barbies and Bags: Reclaimed and Reinvented returns to Sonoma Community Center as a creative fundraiser featuring a gallery exhibit and auction. On view April 3–25\, 2026\, with an opening reception April 3 from 5:30–7:30 PM\, this imaginative show transforms discarded Barbies and other 12-inch dolls into bold works of recycled art. New this year: upcycled\, wearable bags—including clutches\, backpacks\, and more—designed by local artists.    All pieces will be auctioned to benefit the Center\, with a silent auction accessible both in person and online. Submissions are open through March 13\, 2026 (entry fees apply). An all-ages open studio workshop will be held February 15 for those seeking space\, supplies\, or guidance (registration required). The exhibit in Gallery 212 is free and open to the public.
URL:https://www.sonoma.com/event/trashion-barbies-bags-at-sonoma-community-center/
LOCATION:276 East Napa Street, Sonoma, CA, 95476, United States
CATEGORIES:Art Exhibit,Arts,Family Friendly,Sonoma County
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://winecountry-media.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2026/02/14204136/trashion-barbie-1151x1536-1.png
END:VEVENT
